'''ChristianCinema.com, Inc.''' is a [[Christian film|Christian]] [[Filmmaking|film production]] and [[Distribution (business)|distribution]] company founded in 1999, by brothers [[Bobby Downes]] and [[Kevin Downes]].<ref name="Bee">{{cite web |url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-7179523_ITM |title=Visalia, Calif.-based film company helps tell Christian tales |last=Fonte |first=Diwata |date=November 13, 2004 |work=[[The Fresno Bee]] |accessdate=March 28, 2009}}</ref> In addition, the website reviews both [[Movie theater|theatrical]] and [[DVD]] released movies<ref name="Bee"/> (over 6000 currently), carries news articles about Christian film and media, and often interviews filmmakers. It is also an online store for Christian films, with over 1,300 Christian-themed movies, and it distributes them worldwide.

== History ==
ChristianCinema.com was founded in 1999 in [[Visalia, California]], by brothers, [[Kevin Downes|Kevin]] and [[Bobby Downes]] (who is also a [[CEO]]), and their friend Geoff Ludlow. They wanted to make movies and create a system for [[independent film]]makers to [[Film distribution|distribute]] their films.<ref name="Bee"/> Bobby designed the website in the small house where he lived, Kevin shipped the first movie from his home, and they three produced their first movie, ''[[The Moment After]],'' the same year.<ref name="Eagle"/> It has been shown on the [[Trinity Broadcasting Network]], and its website gives filmmakers a place to submit screening copies of their work with the possibility of being distributed and promoted by the website.<ref name="Eagle"/> The company now has its own warehouse and 13 employees.<ref name="Bee"/> Angela Walker (director of producer relations) sends a weekly e-[[newsletter]] to almost 28,000 people, with recommendations about new releases and more.<ref name="VB">{{cite web |url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-33307246_ITM |title=Web savvy retailing |last=Wilde |first=Carol |date=October 29, 2007 |publisher=[[Video Business]] |accessdate=April 1, 2009}}</ref> Jared Geesey is the Vice President of marketing for ChristianCinema.com.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-18716157_ITM |title=Inspiration wrapped up |last=Wilde |first=Carol |date=September 25, 2006 |publisher=[[Video Business]] |accessdate=April 1, 2009}}</ref>

== Online store ==
ChristianCinema.com is also an online store for Christian films, and carries only Christian-oriented and [[Family film|family-friendly films]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.boston.com/business/articles/2006/08/27/netflix_spawns_a_mailbox_full_of_imitators/ |title=Netflix spawns a mailbox full of imitators |date=August 27, 2006 |work=[[The Boston Globe]] |accessdate=March 28, 2009}}</ref> It calls itself "the biggest Christian movie store on the planet,"<ref name="Eagle">{{cite web |url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-30901142_ITM |title=Religion and media column |last=Castillo |first=Brent |date=May 30, 2007 |work=[[The Wichita Eagle]] |accessdate=March 28, 2009}}</ref> with, in 2007, over 1,300 Christian-themed movies,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=BX&s_site=sunherald&p_multi=BX&p_theme=realcities&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=1199B7FF66F9BCC8&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D |title=Christian Cinema Available Online |date=June 1, 2007 |work=[[The Sun Herald]] |accessdate=March 28, 2009}}</ref> and it distributes them worldwide.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-21651298_ITM |title=Brigham Young U.: Moviemakers target Christian audience |last=Bylund |first=Jennilyn |date=June 14, 2004 |work=The America's Intelligence Wire |accessdate=April 1, 2009}}</ref> Many of ChristianCinema.com's members are churches that have weekly or monthly movie nights.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.boston.com/business/articles/2006/08/27/netflix_spawns_a_mailbox_full_of_imitators/ |title=Netflix spawns a mailbox full of imitators |last=Kirsner |first=Scott |date=August 27, 2006 |work=[[The Boston Globe]] |accessdate=April 1, 2009}}</ref> It has a DVD Rental Club that works similar to [[Netflix]], with monthly rates, free shipping and no late fees.<ref name="VB"/> Club members can buy the DVDs or check out two to five films at a time.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pe.com/lifestyles/stories/PE_Fea_Daily_D_dvdclub0611.b64fcbd.html |title=Join the Club |last=Blatter |first=Helene |date=June 10, 2006 |work=[[The Press-Enterprise]] |accessdate=April 1, 2009}}</ref>

== Filmography ==
They have created or worked on the following films:
* ''[[The Moment After]]'' (1999)
* ''[[Mercy Streets]]'' (2000)
* ''[[Lay It Down (film)|Lay It Down]]'' (2001)
* ''[[Time Changer]]'' (2002)
* ''[[Six: The Mark Unleashed]]'' (2003)
* ''[[The Moment After II]]'' (2006)
* ''[[The Visitation (film)|The Visitation]]'' (2006)

